Produce a markdown document with these sections:

## 1. Campaign Overview
One paragraph: what this campaign is, what it must accomplish, and why it matters to the audience.

## 2. Target Audience
Specific role/segment, not "everyone". Include what they care about visually and what will make them stop scrolling.

## 3. Creative Direction
3-5 sentences describing the visual mood, energy, and style. Reference specific visual techniques — not abstract adjectives.

## 4. Mandatory Design Constraints
Bullet list of non-negotiable rules (brand colors, logo clearspace, accessibility minimums, file format requirements).

## 5. Deliverables
Table: deliverable | dimensions | format | quantity | due

## 6. Success Criteria
How will we judge whether this design succeeded? Name 3-5 specific, observable outcomes.

## 7. What This Is Not
Three anti-directions — visual territories explicitly out of scope.

Tone: Direct, specific, opinionated. No clichés ("seamless", "bold and beautiful", "clean and modern" are forbidden as standalone descriptors — always say what they mean concretely).

